Sentencing hearing on June 14, 2017 at 11:00 am.

CO: RMW, REP: Drost, CLERK: Liddle ADA:  Alexis S. Mckinley   DF ATTY:  Jeremiah James Harrelson   DF:  Jennifer Ann Clark appeared. JURY TRIAL DAY 2. Case called at 8:33 a.m. outside the presence of the jury. Court addresses Exhibit #56. ADA McKinley wanted to offer and receive it and publish to the jury. Atty Harrelson objected. ADA McKinley will be addressing only relevant portions. Atty Harrelson gives argument. ADA McKinley would like to address the letter and the dates found in notebook. Atty Harrelson objects to Other Acts Evidence. Court reviews notebook. Atty Harrelson responds. Court will allow portions for knowledge and intent. Court will overrule defenses objection. Jury present at 8:50 a.m. ADA McKinley recalls Deputy Hart to the Stand. S/T Brandy Hart. Direct by ADA McKinley. O/R Exhibit #56 and permission granted to publish portions to the jury. PL Exhibit #59 (Notebook with a chevron pattern). O/R Exhibit #59. PL Exhibit #51 (Supplemental evidence list). O/R Exhibit #51. PL Exhibit #53 (Green folder). O/R Exhibit #53. PL Exhibit #54 (Contents of Green Folder). O/R Exhibit #54. Cross by Atty Harrelson. Witness excused. State calls Investigator Rose to the Stand. S/T Cary Rose. Investigator with the St Croix County Sheriffs Department. Direct by ADA McKinley. PL Exhibit #37 (Supplemental report). O/R Exhibit #37. PL Exhibit #50 (Photocopy of picture of some items found in garbage). O/R Exhibit #50. PL Exhibit's #38 and #39 (Photo of items found in garbage). O/R Exhibit's #38 & #39. PL Exhibit #40 (counterfeit bill with Happy Mothers Day printed on bill). O/R Exhibit #40. PL Exhibit #43 (Photograph of $20.00 bills). O/R Exhibit #43. PL Exhibit #47 (Photo of envelope found in garbage). O/R Exhibit #47. PL Exhibit #55 (Item's found in garbage). O/R Exhibit #55. SIDE BAR. Court will take a short recess. Jury excused at 9:39 a.m. Case recalled and jury present at 9:48 a.m. Investigator Rose retakes the Stand. Cross by Atty Harrelson. Redirect by ADA McKinley. Witness excused. State calls Brianne S. to the Stand. S/T Brianne S. Direct by ADA McKinley. Witness identifies DE in the courtroom. Cross by Atty Harrelson. SIDE BAR. State calls Chief Yalik to the Stand. S/T Craig Yalik. Direct by ADA McKinley. PL Exhibit #112 ( Evidence bag with counterfeit $20.00 bill used at Farm Supply Store). O/R Exhibit #112. Cross by Atty Harrelson. Witness excused. State calls Investigator Haefner to the Stand. S/T James Haefner. Direct by ADA McKinley. SIDE BAR. Cross by Atty Harrelson. DE Exhibit #1006 (Evidence report). O/R Exhibit #1006. SIDE BAR. Witness excused. State rests. Jury excused at 10:31 a.m. On the record outside the presence of the jury. Atty Harrelson makes a Motion to Dismiss of all or some of the charges based on the State's lack of evidence. ADA McKinley gives argument and requesting court deny motion. Court will DENY Motion to Dismiss. Court will recess at 10:37 a.m. Case recalled at 10:51 a.m. outside the presence of the jury. Court makes record of previous Side Bar. Atty Harrelson states DE wishes to testify. Court reviews rights with DE to remain silent. DE understands, waives right to remain silent and wishes to testify. Court finds DE freely, knowingly and intelligently waives right to remain silent. Jury present at 10:57 a.m. Atty Harrelson calls Adam Schottle to the Stand. S/T Adam Schottle. Direct by Atty Harrelson. SIDE BAR. Cross by ADA McKinley. Redirect by Atty Harrelson. Witness excused. Atty Harrelson calls Jennifer Clark to the Stand. S/T Jennifer Clark. Direct by Atty Harrelson. Court will recess for lunch at 12:10 p.m. Jury excused. Case recalled at 1:15 p.m. Jury present. Jennifer Clark retakes the Stand still under Oath. Cross by ADA McKinley. Redirect by Atty Harrelson. Witness excused. Rebuttal by the State. ADA McKinley calls Investigator Mikla to the Stand. S/T Jim Mikla. Investigator with St Croix County Sheriff's Department. Direct by ADA McKinley. SIDE BAR. State calls Investigator Fayerweather to the Stand. S/T Dean Fayerweather. Investigator with St Croix County Sheriff's Department. Cross by Atty Harrelson. Witness excused. Evidence is closed at 1:50 p.m. Jury excused at 1:51 p.m. On the record outside the presence of the jury. Court and parties review Verdicts and Jury Instructions. On the record outside the presence of the Jury at 2:14 p.m. Jury present at 2:15 p.m. Jurors given copies of jury instructions. Jury Instructions given by the Court at 2:19 p.m. Closing argument by ADA McKinley at 2:41 p.m. Closing argument by Atty Harrelson at 2:58 p.m. Rebuttal argument by ADA McKinley at 3:18 p.m. Oath to Bailiff given at 3:38 p.m. Court reads the name of the alternate juror. Alternate juror is excused. Jury excused to deliberate at 3:40 p.m. Court adjourned at 3:41 p.m. Case recalled at 4:46 p.m. outside the presence of the jury. Court has received request from jury for evidence. Parties respond. Court will send Exhibit's #21, #22 & #24 to jury. Court recesses at 4:51 p.m. Case recalled at 5:25 p.m. outside the presence of the jury. Court received another question from the jury. Atty Harrelson responds. Court responds. Attorney's to review Exhibits. Court will bring jury in and have them review the Exhibits #26 & #27 with Chief Yalik removing from the Evidence bags. Exhibit's #25 & #112 will then be shown. There will be no question and answer. Jury present at 5:38 p.m. Court addresses Jury on the display of the Exhibit's. Jury excused at 5:47 p.m. to deliberate. Case recalled at 7:20 p.m. outside the presence of the jury. Court received 2 additional questions from the Jury. Exhibit's #20, #23, #18 and #19 pertain to the jurors question. Parties reach agreement. Court addresses Question 2. Parties agree on answer. Court recesses at 7:24 p.m. Case recalled at 7:56 p.m. with the jury present. Jury has reached a Verdict. We the jury find the DE: 

Ct. 1 GUILTY 
Ct. 2 GUILTY
Ct. 3 GUILTY
Ct. 4 GUILTY

Court polls Jury. Jury excused at 8:01 p.m. Outside the presence of the jury. State requesting court accept Verdict. Court will accept Verdicts. Atty Harrelson has no comment. Court extends PSI deadlines on all files to June 5, 2016. Court will Order a PSI on 15CF374. Bond remains revoked and DE will remain in custody.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for June 14, 2017 at 11:00 am.

CO: RMW, REP: Drost, CLERK: Liddle. ADA:  Alexis S. Mckinley   DF ATTY:  Jeremiah James Harrelson   DF:  Jennifer Ann Clark appeared. JURY TRIAL DAY 1. Case called at 8:32 a.m. Court notes this is Day 1 of a 2 Day Jury Trial. There will be an alternate juror. Each party will get 4 Peremptory Strikes. Atty Harrelson argues number of prior convictions on one of the Witnesses. ADA McKinley gives argument. Court will take testimony of witnesses regarding prior convictions before Brianne S. testifies. Court will recess at 8:37 a.m. Case recalled at 8:58 a.m. outside the presence of the jury. Court reviews the Jury Seating Chart. Possible conflict regarding Juror 505. Parties agree on resolution. Court will replace Juror 505 with Juror 417. Court recesses at 9:01 a.m. Case recalled at 9:12 a.m. with the jury present. Oath of Jurors as to Qualifications given at 9:12 a.m. Voir Dire by the Court at 9:18 a.m. Voir Dire by ADA McKinley at 9:47 a.m. Voir Dire by Atty Harrelson at 10:03 a.m. OFF RECORD. Peremptory Strike at 10:26 a.m. ON THE RECORD at 10:34 a.m. Jury selected and Oath of Juror for Trial given at 10:36 a.m. Court recesses at 10:37 a.m. Case recalled at 10:58 a.m. outside the presence of the jury. Court gave parties copies of preliminary jury instructions. No objections by either party. Court addresses Exhibits. Case recalled at 11:02 a.m. with the jury present. Opening Jury Instructions given by the Court at 11:02 a.m. Opening statement by ADA McKinley at 11:12 a.m. Opening statement by Atty Harrelson at 11:33 a.m. State calls Katie M. to the Stand. S/T Katie M. Direct by ADA McKinley. Witness identifies DE in the courtroom. Cross by Atty Harrelson. Jury excused for lunch at 12:19 p.m. Witness excused. Case recalled at 12:19 p.m. outside the presence of the jury. Atty Harrelson gives argument regarding testimony of Katie M. Requesting to play interview with Chief Yalik. State responds. Court will allow Atty Harrelson to play portions relevant for impeachment purposes or may use transcript. Court recesses at 12:29 p.m. Case recalled at 1:04 p.m. outside the presence of the jury. Atty Harrelson addresses prior convictions regarding Brianne S. Requesting testimony be given. S/T Brianne S. Direct by Atty Harrelson. Witness excused. Atty Harrelson calls Chris G. to the stand. S/T Chris G. Direct by Atty Harrelson. DE Exhibit #1005 (Brianne S. convictions). O/R Exhibit #1005. Witness excused. Atty Harrelson gives argument regarding prior convictions involving Brianne S. ADA McKinley responds. Court will rule on the number of prior convictions is 12. ADA McKinley addresses 2 other issues. Atty Harrelson responds. Case recalled at 1:28 p.m. with the jury present. Katie M. recalled to the Stand. Still under oath. Continued cross by Atty Harrelson. Redirect by ADA McKinley. Witness excused. State calls Deputy Krueger to the Stand. S/T Nick Krueger. Employed as a Deputy with St Croix County Sheriffs Dept. Direct by ADA McKinley. Witness identifies DE in the courtroom. Cross by Atty Harrelson. Witness excused. State calls Chief Yalik to the Stand. S/T Craig Yalik. Employed as a Chief of Police for the City of New Richmond. Direct by ADA McKinley. PL Exhibit #25 ($50.00 bill). O/R Exhibit #25. Permission to publish. PL Exhibit #26 ($20.00 bill). O/R Exhibit #26. PL Exhibit #27 ($20.00 bill). O/R Exhibit #27. PL Exhibit #1 (Evidence Report). O/R Exhibit #1. PL Exhibit #100 (Photograph of bedroom). O/R Exhibit #100. PL Exhibit #3 (Photograph of bedroom). O/R Exhibit #3. PL Exhibit #6(Photograph of shelves with supplies). O/R Exhibit #6. PL Exhibit #28 ($20.00 bill with face on both sides). O/R Exhibit #28. PL Exhibit #7(Photograph of plate with supplies). O/R Exhibit #7. PL Exhibit #29 (Paper with stain). O/R Exhibit #29. PL Exhibit #30 (Counterfeit bills in brown bag). O/R Exhibit #30. PL Exhibit #10 (Photograph of $20.00 bills) and PL Exhibit #13 (Photographs of $20.00 bill). O/R Exhibit's #10 and #13. PL Exhibit #12 (Photograph of multiple $20.00 bills). O/R Exhibit #12. PL Exhibit #101 (Photograph of grocery list). O/R Exhibit #101. DE Exhibit #1003 (FHM Magazine). O/R Exhibit #1003. Court recesses at 2:48 p.m. Case recalled at 3:03 p.m. with the jury present. Continued direct by ADA McKinley. PL Exhibit #14 (Photograph of Evidence). O/R Exhibit #14. PL Exhibit #31 (FHM Magazine with copies of counterfeit bills). O/R Exhibit #31. PL Exhibit's #15, #16 and #107 (Photographs of items found in #31). O/R Exhibit's #15, #16 and #107. Witness identifies DE in the courtroom. PL Exhibit #18 (Photograph of contents of purse found in car) O/R Exhibit #18. PL Exhibit #110 (Photograph of backseat of car). O/R Exhibit #110. PL Exhibit #19 (Photograph of inside of wallet). O/R Exhibit #19. PL Exhibit #20 (Photograph of compartments in wallet). O/R Exhibit #20. PL Exhibit #21 & #22 (Photograph of wallet containing counterfeit bills). O/R Exhibit's #21 & #22. PL Exhibit #32 (Washed $1 bills and $50.00 bill). O/R Exhibit #32. PL Exhibit #33 (2- washed bills found in wallet). O/R Exhibit #33. PL Exhibit #111 (copy of handwritten items that were seized). O/R Exhibit #111. PL Exhibit #34 (2- $20.00 bills and $5.00 bill).
